 Slide 2: Problem Statement

 Title: The Challenge — siRNA Classification from Microscopy Images

 - Task: Predict which siRNA (small interfering RNA) was applied to a cell well
 - Classes: 1,108 different siRNA classes
 - Data: 6-channel fluorescence microscopy images (not standard RGB)
 - Complexity: High intra-class variability due to experimental noise and batch effects
 - Cell Types: HEPG2, HUVEC, RPE, U2OS (4 different cell lines)
 - Sites: Dual imaging sites per well for additional augmentation potential

 Key Challenge: Robust feature extraction across biological replicates with batch effect mitigation

