 Slide 5: Key Architectures — ResNet & DenseNet

 Title: Residual vs. Dense Connectivity

 ResNet-50:
 - Skip connections solve vanishing gradients
 - Bottleneck design: 1×1→3×3→1×1 convolutions
 - Modified stem: 6-channel input adaptation

 DenseNet-121:
 - Dense connectivity: Each layer receives feature maps from all preceding layers
 - Growth rate: 32 new feature maps per layer
 - Feature reuse reduces parameters, improves gradient flow
 - Better generalization on limited training data

 Configuration: AdamW optimizer (lr=3×10⁻⁴), Cosine Annealing, 320×320 images

 ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

 Slide 6: Advanced Architectures

 Title: EfficientNet, ResNeXt, and ConvNeXt

 EfficientNet-B0:
 - Compound scaling (depth, width, resolution)
 - Mobile Inverted Bottleneck (MBConv) blocks
 - Squeeze-and-Excitation (SE) optimization
 - 5.3M parameters (vs. ResNet-50's 25.6M)

 ResNeXt-50 (32×4d):
 - Cardinality = 32 parallel paths per block
 - Aggregated residual transformations
 - Greater representational diversity

 ConvNeXt V2 Tiny:
 - Modernized pure-CNN with Transformer-like design
 - 7×7 depthwise convolutions + Global Response Normalization (GRN)

 ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

 Slide 7: Novel Approaches

 Title: Chaotic CNN & Vision Transformer

 Chaotic CNN (DenseNet-121 + Chaos Theory):
 - Integrated chaotic dynamical systems for feature modulation
 - Skew-Tent Map: Piecewise linear chaotic map
 - Logistic Map: xₙ₊₁ = μxₙ(1-xₙ), μ=4
 - Sine Map: Nonlinear sinusoidal dynamics
 - Goal: Capture complex nonlinear patterns via deterministic chaos

 Vision Transformer (ViT-Base/16):
 - 16×16 patch embeddings
 - 12 Transformer layers, 12 attention heads
 - 86M parameters
 - Mixed precision (FP16) training

