 Slide 11: Key Findings

 Title: Critical Observations

 1. Best Performer: ResNeXt-50 achieved 55.07% — aggregated transformations + all cell types training
 2. DenseNet Superiority: DenseNet-121 (47.42%) outperformed ResNet-50 (37.49%) due to feature reuse and better generalization
 3. Augmentation Impact: Data augmentation + TTA improved DenseNet from 46.65% → 47.42%
 4. Cell Type Strategy: Training on all 4 cell types improved generalization (ResNeXt-50, EfficientNet-B0)
 5. Transformer Failure: ViT and ConvNeXt failed (<1.1%) — lack of inductive bias for microscopy, need for large-scale pretraining
 6. Chaotic CNN: Moderate success (30–34%), but no improvement over standard DenseNet
 7. EfficientNet-B4: Severe overfitting without augmentation (10.83%, nan loss)

