 Slide 13: What Worked vs. What Didn't

 Title: Successes and Failures

 ✅ Successful Approaches:
 - ResNeXt-50 with aggregated residual transformations
 - DenseNet-121 with dense connectivity and augmentation
 - Multi-cell-type training (better generalization)
 - Test-Time Augmentation (TTA) for inference
 - Two-phase training (frozen → unfrozen backbone)

 ❌ Failed Approaches:
 - ViT-Base/16: Requires massive pretraining data
 - ConvNeXt V2: Transfer learning from ImageNet ineffective for 6-channel microscopy
 - EfficientNet-B4 without augmentation: Severe overfitting
 - Chaotic CNN: Chaos theory didn't provide tangible benefits
 - Inception V3: Slow convergence, poor final performance

