 Slide 14: Conclusion

 Title: Summary and Takeaways

 - Best Model: ResNeXt-50 (55.07% validation accuracy) with 30 epochs on all cell types
 - Runner-up: DenseNet-121 (47.42%) with augmentation and TTA
 - Key Insight: Dense connectivity and aggregated transformations outperform simple residual connections for cellular imaging
 - Critical Factor: Training on diverse cell types improves generalization across biological conditions
 - Transformer Warning: Vision Transformers require careful adaptation for domain-specific microscopy data

 Future Directions:
 - Dual-site training (combine Site 1 and Site 2 images)
 - Metric learning with ArcFace loss for better class separation
 - Advanced TTA strategies
 - Domain adaptation for batch effect reduction

